liate.insider.com%3Fh%3Def095c49c5efaf61d3e883181de319ff647329aa7cfbbbc61a6e6850540a3dd1%26postID%3D673f8f74c711dce4fc8c27a8%26postSlug%3Dearly-employee-at-facebook-teaching-kids-about-money-2024-12%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FReasonably-Happy-Essays-Money-Things%252Fdp%252F0997270659%252Fref%253Dsr_1_1%253Fcrid%253D2QCKFU90OR6I1%2526dib%253DeyJ2IjoiMSJ9.3eKtvpJE1cJrgM-MmUyR2WOc07OrDr8QtPINA9u0mC0.O9HloIW9IP6gfwcHVAwa14oSJ7nvn7aKu58BLUQLYVY%2526dib_tag%253Dse%2526keywords%253Dreasonably%252Bhappy%252Bpaul%252Bollinger%2526qid%253D1732128097%2526sprefix%253Dreasonably%252Bhappy%252Bpaul%25252Caps%25252C134%2526sr%253D8-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EReasonably%20Happy%3A%20The%20Skeptics%20Guide%20to%20Achievable%20Contentment%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3E.%26quot%3B%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-things-to-do-atlanta-georgia-according-to-local-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Egrew%20up%20one%20of%20six%20kids%20in%20Atlanta%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20When%20I%20was%20around%2011%2C%20my%20dad%20was%20taking%20me%20to%20get%20my%20first%20cavity%20filled.%20I%20was%20super%20nervous%2C%20but%20my%20dad%2C%20it%20turns%20out%2C%20was%20thinking%20about%20money.%20As%20we%20walked%20in%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BDon't%20get%20the%20novocaine.%20It's%20%2420.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20anecdote%20sums%20up%20everything%20about%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-parents-should-teach-kids-about-money-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efinances%20in%20my%20childhood%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Ehome.%20My%20father%20worked%20for%20the%20power%20company%2C%20so%20he%20always%20had%20a%20job%2C%20but%20he%20was%20never%20rich.%20I%20had%20everything%20I%20needed%2C%20but%20scarcity%20was%20the%20subtext%20of%20our%20economic%20reality.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat's%20very%20different%20from%20how%20my%20own%20kids%2C%20who%20are%2013%20and%2015%2C%20are%20being%20raised.%20I%20was%20one%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-important-facebook-employees-where-are-they-now-2019-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efirst%20250%20employees%20at%20Facebook%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20I%20left%20the%20company%20about%2013%20years%20ago%2C%20but%20due%20to%20good%20pay%20and%20stock%20options%2C%20I'll%20likely%20never%20need%20to%20work%20again%20as%20long%20as%20I%20make%20smart%20choices.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c311b0f2-06df-4c4e-8396-9d80cda7d984%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20son%20asked%20if%20we%20were%20hiring%20a%20private%20chef%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20means%20my%20kids%20are%20growing%20up%20in%20a%20very%20different%20financial%20reality.%20When%20my%20son%20was%207%2C%20he%20came%20home%20from%20one%20of%20his%20even%20richer%20friend's%20house.%20He%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWhen%20are%20we%20going%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-chef-surprising-things-about-job-meredith-hayden-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehire%20a%20chef%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20reaction%20in%20my%20head%20is%20one%20I%20can't%20repeat%20here.%20I%20wanted%20to%20yell%2C%20%26quot%3BA%20chef%3F%20The%20only%20chef%20I%20grew%20up%20with%20was%20Chef%20Boyardee!%26quot%3B%20But%20I%20realized%20my%20son%20only%20knew%20what%20he%20sees.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20joked%20about%20sending%20my%20kids%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstates-where-middle-class-income-earners-pay-most-taxes-income-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emiddle-class%20camp%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20at%20Grandpa's%2C%20where%20they%20had%20to%20face%20horrors%20like%20having%20a%20fan%20instead%20of%20air%20conditioning.%20I%20approach%20the%20difference%20between%20my%20upbringing%20and%20theirs%20with%20humor%2C%20but%20the%20truth%20is%20no%20one%20imagines%20raising%20kids%20in%20an%20economic%20situation%20that's%20so%20vastly%20different%20from%20how%20they%20were%20raised.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e7bc14b2-24b8-4fa1-ae34-8c94ccb43198%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20want%20my%20kids%20to%20learn%20to%20prioritize%20financial%20decisions%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20book%20that's%20helped%20me%20greatly%20is%20%26quot%3BThe%20Opposite%20of%20Spoiled%26quot%3B%20by%20Ron%20Lieber.%20He%20talks%20about%20the%20importance%20of%20giving%20kids%20allowance%2C%20because%20that%20allows%20them%20to%20make%20mistakes%20with%20small%20amounts%20of%20money.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20wife%20and%20I%20give%20the%20kids%20a%20modest%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-budget-tips-teenagers-give-allowance-vacation-economy-inflation-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emonthly%20allowance%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20That%20means%20we%20don't%20have%20to%20talk%20with%20them%20about%20money%20every%20day%2C%20and%20they%20weigh%20up%20whether%20they%20really%20want%20something%2C%20like%20a%20new%20soccer%20ball.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt's%20important%20to%20me%20that%20the%20kids%20know%20that%20money%20isn't%20in%20endless%20supply.%20If%20they%20buy%20X%2C%20they%20might%20not%20have%20enough%20money%20to%20buy%20Y.%20Although%20I%20have%20substantial%20wealth%2C%20I%20still%20prioritize%20my%20financial%20decisions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20example%2C%20I%20could%20fly%20private%2C%20but%20that%20would%20require%20me%20to%20work%20in%20a%20traditional%20job%20to%20have%20more%20income%20coming%20in.%20Yet%2C%20it's%20more%20important%20to%20me%20to%20be%20able%20to%20do%20the%20type%20of%20work%20I%20enjoy%2C%20comedy%2C%20which%20happens%20to%20pay%20less.%20I%20value%20professional%20flexibility%20more%20than%20the%20status%20of%20flying%20private%20or%20the%20joys%20of%20getting%20to%20skip%20TSA%2C%20so%20I%20prioritize%20that.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fc058f79-a125-4064-9b81-9064491e9d5a%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EFinancial%20security%20has%20let%20me%20chase%20my%20dream%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI've%20loved%20comedy%20since%20I%20first%20got%20onstage%20at%20Dartmouth%20College%20during%20grad%20school.%20My%20parents%20paid%20for%20college%2C%20but%20I%20had%20%2480%2C000%20in%20student%20loans%20for%20graduate%20school%20back%20in%201997.%20That%20financial%20reality%20meant%20that%20I%20had%20to%20take%20a%20traditional%20job%20in%20the%20tech%20world%20rather%20than%20chase%20my%20dream%20of%20being%20a%20comedian.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20working%20in%20tech%20for%20a%20few%20years%20and%20paying%20off%20my%20student%20loans%2C%20I%20quit%20to%20pursue%20comedy%20full%20time%20for%20two%20years.%20My%20standard%20of%20living%20was%20still%20good%20because%20I%20had%20a%20lot%20saved.%20But%20when%20I%20met%20my%20wife%20and%20knew%20we%20wanted%20kids%2C%20I%20returned%20to%20the%20tech%20world%20because%20I%20wanted%20more%20financial%20security%20than%20life%20as%20a%20standup%20comedian%20could%20give%20me.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWorking%20at%20Facebook%20ended%20up%20being%20a%20bigger%20home%20run%20than%20I%20could%20have%20ever%20imagined.%20I%20remember%20saying%20to%20my%20wife%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20might%20be%20as%20big%20as%20MySpace%20one%20day.%26quot%3B%20I%20couldn't%20even%20imagine%20how%20big%20Facebook%20would%20become%20or%20the%20changes%20it%20would%20bring%20to%20my%20life.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%20that%20I%20spend%20time%20writing%20jokes%20about%20my%20financial%20situation%20and%20talking%20about%20money%20on%20my%20podcast%2C%20I've%20realized%20that%20happiness%20comes%20from%20making%20a%20choice%20to%20be%20grateful%2C%20not%20from%20a%20number%20in%20your%20accounts.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearly-employee-at-facebook-teaching-kids-about-money-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1735128241000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F673f91d6ede4eeae3928de16%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearly-employee-at-facebook-teaching-kids-about-money-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Paul%20Ollinger%20was%20Facebook's%20vice%20president%20of%20sales%20before%20he%20left%20the%20company.%20He%20gives%20his%20teens%20a%20modest%20allowance%20and%20is%20not%20an%20endless%20supply.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Kelly%20Burch)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearly-employee-at-facebook-teaching-kids-about-money-2024-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%2232%20Passengers%2C%20Including%20Girl%2C%2011%2C%20Survive%20Azerbaijan%20Airlines%20Plane%20Crash%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThirty-two%20people%20survived%20the%20initial%20impact%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fplane-with-110-on-board-crashes-near-aktau-city-in-kazakhstan-bursts-into-flames-7327948%23pfrom%3Dhome-ndtv_topscroll%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20plane%20crash%20in%20Kazakhstan's%20Aqtau%20city%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0Wednesday%20afternoon.%20Twenty-two%2C%20including%20a%2011-year-old%20girl%20and%20a%2016-year-old%20teen%2C%20were%20hospitalised.%3C%2Fp