ects%20are%20expected%20to%20pass%20each%20other%20at%20a%20close%20distance.%20Only%20a%20small%20fraction%20of%20warnings%20actually%20end%20in%20a%20collision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20space%20objects%20do%20collide%2C%20they%20eject%20high-speed%20debris%20in%20multiple%20directions%2C%20creating%20a%20new%20zone%20of%20hazardous%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdish-network-fined-first-ever-fcc-enforcement-against-space-junk-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejunk%20in%20orbit%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22320%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22satellite%20debris%20collision%20experiment%20simulation%20explosion%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e309f3624306a1aa21951f7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22240%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20projectile%20strikes%20a%20mock-up%20of%20a%20spacecraft%20in%20a%20NASA-Air%20Force%20test%20meant%20to%20simulate%20space%20debris%20collisions.%3Cp%3EArnold%20Engineering%20Development%20Complex%2FAir%20Force%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20could%20generate%20a%20chain%20reaction%2C%20an%20unstoppable%20chain%20reaction%20of%20further%20collisions%2C%20ultimately%20resulting%20in%20a%20completely%20filled-up%20space%20environment%2C%26quot%3B%20Berger%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20worst-case%20scenario%2C%20orbit%20could%20become%20so%20crowded%20that%20there's%20no%20safe%20space%20for%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-spacex-starship-launch-five-huge-deal-space-travel-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erocket%20launches%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20situation%20experts%20call%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspace-junk-kessler-syndrome-chain-reaction-prevention-2018-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKessler%20syndrome%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bthat%20we%20hope%20to%20prevent%2C%26quot%3B%20Berger%20