0to%20conceive%20a%20thought%2C%20to%20speak%20it%2C%20and%20by%20doing%20so%20to%20make%20it%20true.'%20At%20long%20last.%20%40SalmanRushdie's%20The%20Satanic%20Verses%20is%20allowed%20to%20be%20sold%20in%20India%20after%20a%2036-year%20ban.%20Here%20it%20is%20at%20Bahrisons%20Bookstore%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20bookstores%2C%20including%20Midland%20Book%20Shop%20and%20Om%20Book%20Shop%2C%20do%20not%20plan%20to%20import%20the%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20November%2C%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20closed%20the%20proceedings%20on%20a%20petition%20challenging%20the%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20government's%20ban%20on%20the%20import%20of%20the%20novel%2C%20saying%20since%20authorities%20have%20failed%20to%20produce%20the%20relevant%20notification%2C%20it%20has%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bpresumed%20that%20it%20does%20not%20exist%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20order%20came%20after%20government%20authorities%20failed%20to%20submit%20the%20notification%20dated%20October%205%2C%201988%2C%20which%20banned%20the%20import%20of%20the%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20light%20of%20the%20aforesaid%20circumstances%2C%20we%20have%20no%20other%20option%20except%20to%20presume%20that%20no%20such%20notification%20exists%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20we%20cannot%20examine%20the%20validity%20thereof%20and%20dispose%20of%20the%20writ%20petition%20as%20infructuous%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20book%20ran%20into%20trouble%20shortly%20after%20its%20publication%2C%20eventually%20leading%20to%20Iranian%20leader%20Ruhollah%20Khomeini%20issuing%20a%20fatwa%20calling%20on%20Muslims%20to%20kill%20Rushdie%20and%20his%20publishers.%20Rushdie%20spent%20nearly%2010%20years%20in%20hiding%20in%20the%20UK%20and%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20July%201991%2C%20the%20novelist's%20Japanese%20translator%20Hitoshi%20Igarashi%20was%20killed%20in%20his%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20August%2012%2C%202022%2C%20Lebanese-American%20Hadi%20Matar%20stabbed%20Rushdie%20on%20stage%20at%20a%20lecture%2C%20leaving%20him%20blind%20in%20one%20eye.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20the%20book%20is%20available%20for%20purchase%20at%20Bahrisons%2C%20it%20evoked%20a%20mixed%20response%20from%20readers%2C%20especially%20due%20to%20its%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBala%20Sundaresan%2C%20a%20tech%20entrepreneur%2C%20who%20has%20always%20wanted%20a%20physical%20copy%20of%20the%20book%20was%20surprised%20to%20hear%20the%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20rather%20wait%20some%20more%20time%20till%20an%20Indian%20print%20of%20the%20book%20is%20available.%20I%20was%20only%20interested%20in%20it%20because%20of%20the%20controversy%20that%20has%20surrounded%20it%20for%20decades%2C%20(I%20am)%20not%20really%20a%20Rushdie%20fan%2C%26quot%3B%20the%2033-year-old%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJayesh%20Verma%2C%20a%2024-year-old%20Delhi%20University%20student%2C%20said%20it%20only%20makes%20sense%20for%20a%20collector%20or%20a%20%26quot%3Bdie-hard%26quot%3B%20Rushdie%20fan%20to%20buy%20the%20book%20at%20its%20current%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20be%20honest%2C%20those%20who%20wanted%20to%20read%20it%20because%20of%20all%20the%20controversy%20have%20already%20read%20it%20by%20downloading%20a%20soft%20copy.%20Anyone%20else%20who%20buys%20it%20for%20Rs%202%2C000%20has%20to%20be%20a%20collector%20or%20a%20die-hard%20fan%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20some%20like%20literature%20student%20Rashmi%20Chatterjee%20plan%20to%20buy%20the%20book%20for%20%26quot%3Bits%20place%20in%20India's%20literary%20history%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20ignore%20the%20book%2C%20let%20alone%20its%20literary%20merit.%20It%20should%20be%20bought%20solely%20for%20being%20an%20argument%20against%20censorship.%20It%20marks%20a%20critical%20point%20in%20India's%20literary%20history%2C%26quot%3B%20the%2022-year-old%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1735123080000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fm92rrqcg_satanic-verses-_625x300_25_December_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsalman-rushdies-the-satanic-verses-returns-to-india-after-36-year-ban-7328796%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22British-Indian%20novelist%20Salman%20Rushdie's%20controversial%20book%20%26quot%3BThe%20Satanic%20Verses%26quot%3B%20has%20quietly%20returned%20to%20India%2036%20years%20after%20it%20was%20banned%20by%20the%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20government.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsalman-rushdies-the-satanic-verses-returns-to-india-after-36-year-ban-7328796%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Varun%20clarifies%20viral%20kiss%20with%20Kiara%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1735122967000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-116654170%2Cimgsize-35194.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fbaby-johns-actor-varun-dhawan-clarifies-viral-kiss-with-kiara-advani-it-was-planned-all-in-good-fun%2Farticleshow%2F116654174.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F116654174.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EVarun%20Dhawan%20addresses%20recent%20controversies%20of%20kissing%20Kiara%20Advani%20and%20touching%20Alia%20Bhatt%E2%80%99s%20belly%2C%20clarifying%20that%20interactions%20were%20either%20planned%20or%20innocent.%20He%20explains%20enjoying%20playful%20interactions%20in%20a%20positive%20environment%2C%20whether%20with%20male%20or%20female%20co-stars.%20Varun%20emphasized%20his%20intentions%20were%20never%20inappropriate%20and%20revealed%20details%20about%20his%20recent%20film%20'Baby%20John.'%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fbaby-johns-actor-varun-dhawan-clarifies-viral-kiss-with-kiara-advani-it-was-planned-all-in-good-fun%2Farticleshow%2F116654174.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Why%20Crowning%20Bangladesh%20'Country%20Of%20The%20Year'%20Is%20Worrying%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2F75t4s75_bangladesh-protest-reuters_625x300_12_December_24.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Economist%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehas%20chosen%20Bangladesh%20as%20the%20country%20of%20the%20year.%20In%20view%20of%20this%20mouthpiece%20of%20the%20British%20establishment%2C%20the%20regime%20change%20in%20Bangladesh%20is%20a%20positive%20development%20not%20only%20for%20Bangladesh%20but%20also%20for%20the%20international%20community%20as%20a%20whole.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBangladesh%20has%20won%20this%20British%20accolade%20outcompeting%20other%20contenders%20such%20as%20Poland%2C%20South%20Africa%2C%20Argentina%20and%20Syria.%20This%20is%20odd%20in%20itself%20as%20one%20can%20see%20no%20discernible%20British%20stake%20in%20Bangladesh%20that%20is%20more%20important%20than%20the%20ouster%20of%20Assad%20from%20Syria%20or%20the%20importance%20of%20Tusk%20assuming%20power%20in%20Poland%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20Ukraine%20conflict%2C%20in%20which%20the%20UK%20is%20fully%20involved.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWest's%20Hypocrisy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20antipathy%20of%20the%20US%20and%20the%20UK%20towards%20Sheikh%20Hasina%20is%20well%20known.%20Her%20ouster%20has%20been%20encouraged%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20she%20had%20suppressed%20democracy%20in%20Bangladesh.%20Why%20should%20the%20issue%20of%20democracy%20in%20Bangladesh%20have%20such%20importance%20for%20distant%2C%20non-regional%20countries%3F%20Whether%20Bangladesh%20is%20a%20democracy%20or%20not%20does%20not%20impact%20any%20decipherable%20US%20or%20UK%20stake%20in%20the%20country%20that%20could%20be%20considered%20vital%20for%20their%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20hypocrisy%20in%20the%20American%20and%20British%20discourse%20on%20democracy%20is%20manifest.%20Both%20the%20US%20and%20the%20UK%20maintain%20very%20close%20ties%20with%20countries%20that%20are%20not%20only%20not%20democratic%20but%20do%20not%20even%20hold%20elections%E2%80%94however%20flawed%E2%80%94or%20allow%20political%20dissent%2C%20much%20less%20permit%20the%20existence%20of%20political%20parties.%20Many%20are%20monarchies%20or%20military%20dictatorships%20or%20are%20ruled%20by%20communist%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20is%20not%20a%20democracy%20but%20the%20West%20has%20flourishing%20relations%20with%20it.%20The%20US%20and%20the%20UK%20have%20not%20made%20democracy%20an%20issue%20in%20their%20ties%20with%20Vietnam%2C%20for%20example.%20The%20Biden%20government%20did%20not%20invite%20Singapore%20to%20the%20two%20Summits%20for%20Democracy%20that%20it%20had%20organised.%20This%20did%20not%2C%20however%2C%20lead%20to%20efforts%20by%20the%20West%20to%20make%20the%20Singapore%20polity%20more%20democratic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBullying%20Countries%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20is%20therefore%20not%20one%20of%20countries%20adhering%20to%20democracy%20or%20Western%20values%20for%20them%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20acceptable%20partners.%20It%20is%20essentially%20a%20form%20of%20political%20bullying%20of%20weak%20countries%20at%20little%20cost.%3Cbr%3E%5CnMyanmar%20has%20long%20been%20targeted%20by%20the%20US%20with%20sanctions%20because%20of%20the%20grip%20its%20military%20junta%20has%20retained%20over%20the%20country's%20political%20system.%20That%20this%20has%20pushed%20Myanmar%20increasingly%20into%20the%20arms%20of%20China%20and%20damaged%20our%20strategic%20interests%20in%20that%20country%20has%20been%20ignored%20by%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20case%20of%20Bangladesh%2C%20too%2C%20the%20impact%20of%20Sheikh%20Hasina's%20ouster%20on%20India's%20vital%20strategic%20interests%20in%20that%20country%20has%20been%20ignored.%20Major%20India-Bangladesh%20connectivity%20and%20development%20projects%20were%20implemented%20during%20Sheikh%20Hasina's%20rule%2C%20to%20mutual%20advantage.%20A%20key%20gain%20for%20India%20was%20the%20ouster%20of%20insurgent%20groups%20operating%20from%20Bangladesh%20soil%20against%20India%2C%20an%20issue%20that%20the%20Bangladesh%20Nationalist%20Party%20(BNP)%20government%20in%20Bangladesh%20was%20unwilling%20to%20address.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20regime%20change%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20the%20doors%20are%20also%20being%20opened%20for%20increased%20Chinese%20influence.%20Why%20should%20the%20stakes%20of%20the%20US%20and%20the%20UK%20in%20Bangladesh%20be%20more%20important%20than%20those%20of%20India%2C%20its%20immediate%20neighbour%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIgnoring%20India's%20Concerns%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20British%20(and%20the%20US)%20do%20not%20see%20the%20rise%20of%20Islamist%20forces%20in%20our%20region%20as%20a%20danger%20to%20India's%20security.%20The%20British%20have%20always%20politically%20supported%20Pakistan%20on%20India-Pakistan%20issues.%20They%20have%20not%20taken%20adequate%20cognisance%20of%20Pakistan's%20use%20of%20terrorism%20as%20an%20instrument%20of%20state%20policy%20towards%20India.%20Despite%20the%20increasing%20radicalisation%20of%20Pakistani%20society%2C%20the%20British%20have%20not%20changed%20their%20fundamental%20sympathies%20for%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20insensitivity%20of%20the%20British%20to%20the%20ISI-linked%20activities%20of%20Khalistani%20extremists%20against%20India%20on%20UK%20soil%20is%20part%20of%20this%20syndrome.%20The%20British%20also%20took%20a%20position%20on%20the%20Taliban%20take-over%20of%20Afghanistan%20that%20did%20not%20take%20into%20account%20India's%20concerns.%20This%20is%20true%20of%20US%20policies%20on%20the%20rise%20of%20Islamic%20forces%20in%20our%20region%2C%20including%20facilitating%20the%20return%20of%20the%20Taliban%20to%20power%20in%20Afghanistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20would%20explain%20why%20the%20British%20and%20the%20US%20are%20not%20particularly%20concerned%20about%20the%20Islamist%20forces%20gaining%20power%20in%20Bangladesh.%20Further%20afield%20we%20have%20seen%20how%20the%20West%20is%20welcoming%20the%20takeover%20of%20Syria%20by%20Islamist%20elements%20linked%20in%20the%20past%20to%20al%20Qaeda.%20A%20suitably%20adapted%20narrative%20is%20being%20promoted%20to%20present%20the%20new%20leadership%20in%20a%20new%20political%20and%20sartorial%20attire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Convenient%20Narrative%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20article%20lauding%20the%20regime%20change%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Economist%3C%2Fem%3E%20welcomes%20the%20overthrow%20of%20an%20autocrat.%20This%20convenient%20narrative%20disregards%20the%20fact%20that%20Bangladesh%20has%20had%20long%20spells%20of%20military%20rule.%20The%20BNP%20under%20Begum%20Khaleda%20Zia%20was%2C%20and%20is%2C%20by%20no%20means%20less%20autocratic%2C%20and%20the%20current%20forces%20in%20Bangladesh%20intend%20to%20re-write%20the%20country's%20secular%20constitution%20to%20make%20it%20more%20Islamic.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Economist%20%3C%2Fem%3Erecognises%20that%20the%20BNP%20is%20%E2%80%9Cvenal%E2%80%9D.%20Where%20are%2C%20therefore%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnon-autocratic%E2%80%9D%20or%20genuinely%20democratic%20forces%20in%20Bangladesh%20that%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Economist%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20in%20mind%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Economist%20%3C%2Fem%3Erefers%20to%20%E2%80%9CIslamic%20extremism%E2%80%9D%20as%20a%20threat%2C%20no%20doubt%20believing%20that%20flagging%20it%20pro-forma%20will%20protect%20the%20journal%20from%20being%20accused%20of%20completely%20ignoring%20the%20danger.%20The%20reality%20of%20Islamists%20calling%20the%20shots%20in%20Bangladesh%20is%20being%20overlooked%20to%20suit%20the%20narrative%20building%20on%20the%20change%20in%20power%20there.%20There%20is%20no%20reference%20to%20the%20Jamaat-e-Islami%2C%20which%20is%20active%20on%20the%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20paper%20calls%20for%20holding%20elections%20after%20ensuring%20that%20the%20courts%20are%20neutral.%20That%20seems%20comical%20after%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20has%20been%20hounded%20out%20of%20office%20and%20the%20other%20judges%20are%20being%20coerced%20into%20giving%20the%20kind%20of%20judgments%20that%20the%20mob%20wants.%20It%20also%20says%20the%20Yunus%20government%20must%20ensure%20that%20the%20opposition%20has%20time%20to%20organise.%20Which%20opposition%2C%20when%20the%20Awami%20League%20will%20not%20seemingly%20be%20allowed%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20elections%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20paper%20claims%2C%20contrary%20to%20evidence%2C%20that%20the%20Yunus%20government%20has%20restored%20order%20and%20stabilised%20the%20economy.%20India%20has%20more%20than%20once%20flagged%20its%20concerns%20about%20the%20law%20and%20order%20situation%20on%20the%20ground%20in%20Bangladesh%20and%20the%20persecution%20of%20minorities%20in%20the%20country%2C%20especially%20the%20Hindu%20minority.%20But%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Economist%20%3C%2Fem%3Econveniently%20ignores%20this%2C%20which%20shows%20the%20bad%20journalistic%20faith%20of%20this%20leftover%20of%20British%20imperialist%20hubris.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Kanwal%20Sibal%20was%20Foreign%20Secretary%20and%20Ambassador%20to%20Turkey%2C%20Egypt%2C%20France%20and%20Russia%2C%20and%20Deputy%20Chief%20Of%20Mission%20in%20Washington.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1735122780000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2F75t4s75_bangladesh-protest-reuters_625x300_12_December_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwhy-crowning-bangladesh-as-country-of-the-year-is-worrying-7328995%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20the%20article%20lauding%20the%20regime%20change%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20The%20Economist%20welcomes%20the%20overthrow%20of%20an%20autocrat.%20This%20convenient%20narrative%20disregards%20the%20fact%20that%20Bangladesh%20has%20had%20long%20spells%20of%20military%20rule.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwhy-crowning-bangladesh-as-country-of-the-year-is-worrying-7328995%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Banned%20by%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20govt%2C%20why%20Rushdie's%20book%20is%20now%20being%20sold%20in%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1735122683000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-116654076%2Cimgsize-1124073.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fthe-satanic-verses-salman-rushides-banned-book-now-available-in-india%2Farticleshow%2F116653576.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Salman%20Rushdie's%20banned%20book%20%26quot%3BThe%20Satanic%20Verses%26quot%3B%20is%20now%20available%20in%20limited%20stock%20at%20a%20Delhi%20bookstore.%20The%20ban%2C%20imposed%20in%201988%2C%20ended%20as%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20noted%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20notification.%20Rushdie's%20controversial%20novel%20remains%20highly%20debated%20globally%2C%20and%20its%20release%20has%20reignited%20discussions%20on%20free%20speech%20and%20artistic%20expression.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20N